{"title_page": "IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society", "text_new": "{{Proposed deletion/dated\n  |concern = Non-notable sub-group of notable organisation\n  |timestamp = 20200420133855\n  |help = \n}}\n{{primary|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| image = IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society (logo).png\n| image_size = 100px\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| map = \n| map_size = \n| map_alt = \n| map2_size = \n| map2_alt = \n| motto = \n| predecessor = IEEE Technology Management Council\n| merged = \n| successor = \n| formation = {{start date and age|1951}}\n| extinction = <!-- e.g. use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| type = Non-profit professional organization\n| status = \n| purpose =\n| headquarters = \n| coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline,title}} -->\n| services = \n| language = \n| leader_title = President\n| leader_name = Michael W. Condry\n| leader_title2 = President-elect\n| leader_name2 = TBD\n| leader_name3 = Luke Maki\n| leader_title3 = Immediate Past President\n| leader_title4 = \n| leader_name4 = \n| board_of_directors =\n| key_people = \n| main_organ = \n| parent_organization = [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]]\n| subsidiaries = \n| affiliations = \n| budget = \n| volunteers = \n| slogan = \n| remarks = \n| formerly = \n| footnotes = \n| name = IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society\n| native_name = \n| map_caption = \n| map2 = \n| map2_caption = \n| abbreviation = IEEE TEMS\n| founder = \n| merger = \n| tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for non-profit org) -->\n| registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org -->\n| location = \n| region = \n| products = Publications and conferences on leadership and management\n| methods = \n| fields = \n| membership = \n| owner = <!-- or | owners = -->\n| sec_gen = \n| secessions = \n| revenue = \n| disbursements = \n| expenses = \n| endowment = \n| staff = \n| mission = \n| website = {{url|ieee-tems.org}}\n}}\nThe '''IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society''' (TEMS) was formerly one of seven Councils of the [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]] (IEEE). The Council became the IEEE Technology Engineering and Management Society (TEMS) as of 1 January 2015.\n\n== History ==\nThe Professional Group on Engineering Management was established under the [[Institute of Radio Engineers]] in 1951. This group became the Engineering Management Society (EMS) of the IEEE in 1955. In 2007 this became the IEEE Technology Management Council (TMC) and in January 2015 the Technology Engineering and Management Society.\n\n== Field of interest ==\nThe field of interest encompasses the [[management sciences]] and practices required for defining, implementing, and managing engineering and technology.\n\n=== Publications ===\nThe society publishes two [[peer-reviewed]] journals: the ''[[Transactions on Engineering Management]]'' and the ''[[Engineering Management Review]]''.\n\nSociety also publishes a popular newsletter and magazine : [http://leader.ieee-tems.org/ IEEE Leader]\n\n=== Conferences ===\nThe society sponsors and co-sponsors a number of internationally-held conferences and events on subjects relevant to its field of interest (the flagship one being [http://www.temscon.org/ TEMSCON]).<ref>[http://ieee-tems.org/conferences IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society Conferences]</ref><ref>[http://ieee-tems.org/itmc2014 The International Technology Management Conference (ITMC)]</ref>\n\n== Governance ==\nThe society is governed by an Administrative Committee consisting of officers and members, most of whom are elected by the membership. In addition, the society has Technical Committees dealing with the major management issues.\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.ieee-tems.org}}\n\n{{Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers}}\n\n[[Category:IEEE societies]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1951]]\n", "text_old": "{{primary|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| image = IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society (logo).png\n| image_size = 100px\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| map = \n| map_size = \n| map_alt = \n| map2_size = \n| map2_alt = \n| motto = \n| predecessor = IEEE Technology Management Council\n| merged = \n| successor = \n| formation = {{start date and age|1951}}\n| extinction = <!-- e.g. use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| type = Non-profit professional organization\n| status = \n| purpose =\n| headquarters = \n| coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline,title}} -->\n| services = \n| language = \n| leader_title = President\n| leader_name = Michael W. Condry\n| leader_title2 = President-elect\n| leader_name2 = TBD\n| leader_name3 = Luke Maki\n| leader_title3 = Immediate Past President\n| leader_title4 = \n| leader_name4 = \n| board_of_directors =\n| key_people = \n| main_organ = \n| parent_organization = [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]]\n| subsidiaries = \n| affiliations = \n| budget = \n| volunteers = \n| slogan = \n| remarks = \n| formerly = \n| footnotes = \n| name = IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society\n| native_name = \n| map_caption = \n| map2 = \n| map2_caption = \n| abbreviation = IEEE TEMS\n| founder = \n| merger = \n| tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for non-profit org) -->\n| registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org -->\n| location = \n| region = \n| products = Publications and conferences on leadership and management\n| methods = \n| fields = \n| membership = \n| owner = <!-- or | owners = -->\n| sec_gen = \n| secessions = \n| revenue = \n| disbursements = \n| expenses = \n| endowment = \n| staff = \n| mission = \n| website = {{url|ieee-tems.org}}\n}}\nThe '''IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society''' (TEMS) was formerly one of seven Councils of the [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]] (IEEE). The Council became the IEEE Technology Engineering and Management Society (TEMS) as of 1 January 2015.\n\n== History ==\nThe Professional Group on Engineering Management was established under the [[Institute of Radio Engineers]] in 1951. This group became the Engineering Management Society (EMS) of the IEEE in 1955. In 2007 this became the IEEE Technology Management Council (TMC) and in January 2015 the Technology Engineering and Management Society.\n\n== Field of interest ==\nThe field of interest encompasses the [[management sciences]] and practices required for defining, implementing, and managing engineering and technology.\n\n=== Publications ===\nThe society publishes two [[peer-reviewed]] journals: the ''[[Transactions on Engineering Management]]'' and the ''[[Engineering Management Review]]''.\n\nSociety also publishes a popular newsletter and magazine : [http://leader.ieee-tems.org/ IEEE Leader]\n\n=== Conferences ===\nThe society sponsors and co-sponsors a number of internationally-held conferences and events on subjects relevant to its field of interest (the flagship one being [http://www.temscon.org/ TEMSCON]).<ref>[http://ieee-tems.org/conferences IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society Conferences]</ref><ref>[http://ieee-tems.org/itmc2014 The International Technology Management Conference (ITMC)]</ref>\n\n== Governance ==\nThe society is governed by an Administrative Committee consisting of officers and members, most of whom are elected by the membership. In addition, the society has Technical Committees dealing with the major management issues.\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.ieee-tems.org}}\n\n{{Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers}}\n\n[[Category:IEEE societies]]\n[[Category:Organizations established in 1951]]\n", "name_user": "Fayenatic london", "label": "safe", "comment": "PROD: propose deletion as non-notable  (viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEEE_Technology_and_Engineering_Management_Society"}
{"title_page": "Plabita Borthakur", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=January 2018}}\n[[File:Plabita Borthakur 1.jpg|alt=Plabita Borthakur|thumb|Plabita Borthakur]]\n'''Plabita Borthakur''' is an Indian film actor, singer and an artist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://themoviean.com/plabita-borthakur-interview/|title=The Rockstar 'Burkha' Girl - Plabita Borthakur|publisher=The Moviean|accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/lipstick-under-my-burkha-stars-cast-actress-plabit-borthakur-rehana-abidi-4760212/|title=Girl, You'll be a Woman Soon|website=Indianexpress.com|accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref>{{Infobox person\n| name               = Plabita Borthakur\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_place        = [[Duliajan]], [[Dibrugarh district]], [[Assam]], [[India]]\n| nationality        = [[India]]n\n| education          = Graduate\n| occupation         = Actress, Singer\n| years_active       = 2014 - Present\n| home_town          = [[Guwahati]], [[Kamrup district]], [[Assam]], [[India]]\n| height             = 5 ft 5 in.\n| weight             = 49kg\n| parents            = Probin Borthakur <br> Rina Borthakur\n| relatives          = [[Parineeta Borthakur]] <small>(sister)</small>\n| website            = https://plabitaborthakur.com\n}}\n\n==Early life==\nHer father Probin Borthakur is an Indian classical singer and teacher while her mother is a writer and poet. Her older sisters, [[Parineeta Borthakur]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://themoviean.com/parineeta-borthakur-exclusive-interview/|title=A Woman is the Best Judge for Herself - Parineeta Borthakur|publisher=The Moviean|accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref> and Priyangi Borthakur, are in the film industry as well. She grew up in the Oil India township of Duliajan in Assam, before moving to Mumbai's Jai Hind College, for higher studies. Professionally, she got her head start with numerous ad assignments and concerts with her band, Manu and Chow.\n\n==Career==\nPlabita Borthakur made her debut in ''[[PK (film)|PK]]'' in a blink and miss role as [[Anushka Sharma]]'s sister.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.magicalassam.com/2016/10/plabita-borthakur-assam.html/amp|title= Plabita in Pk|website=Magicalassam.com|accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref> She is back with another [[Bollywood]] film, where she plays one of the main protagonists in the much spoken about, ''[[Lipstick Under My Burkha]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Plabita Borthakur: Indian audience is ready for realistic content - Times of India|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/plabita-borthakur-indian-audience-is-ready-for-realistic-content/articleshow/59790709.cms|accessdate=7 January 2018|work=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 July 2017, she made a special appearance on [[The Kapil Sharma Show]], alongside [[Prakash Jha]] and [[Ekta Kapoor]].\n\nPlabita has received rave reviews for her performance in ''[[Lipstick Under My Burkha]]''.\n\nShe is currently shooting for 2 feature films '''Waah Zindagi''' (under the banner Shivaza Films), and '''Chhote Nawab''' (Yoodlee Films by SaReGaMa). Her webseries, \"[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2J2yXSLgKko '''What's Your Status''']\" released in July, 2018.\n\nShe was part of an episodic web series on Zee5 called '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pPDi566ezgw Parchhayee]''', that released on the 24th of June, 2019.\n\nIn June 2019, the '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mJQjo0K5Fgk trailer of Doosra]''' shows her in a pivotal role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/reel/928675/doosra-trailer-abhinay-deos-cricket-drama-relives-the-shirtless-sourav-ganguly-moment-from-2002|title='Doosra' trailer: Abhinay Deo's cricket drama relives the shirtless Sourav Ganguly moment from 2002|last=Staff|first=Scroll|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-28}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/doosra-poster-abhinay-deo-s-film-relives-sourav-ganguly-s-celebration-of-epic-2002-natwest-series-win-1557086-2019-06-27|title=Doosra poster: Abhinay Deo's film relives Sourav Ganguly's celebration of epic 2002 NatWest Series win|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-06-28|agency=Ist}}</ref>\n\n== Ad Commercials ==\n'''Paytm''': For a long time, Plabita was popular as the [[Paytm|'''PayTM''']] girl, thanks to her [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0eqkQddu-cA '''Paytm Ad'''].\n\nShe has since, done numerous ad commercials.\n\n'''[[Marico]] Livon''': '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lSkwaQt8UYo Link]'''\n\n'''[[Britannia Industries|Britannia]]''': '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ACh7G8U6xh4 Link]'''\n\n'''[[Paper Boat]]: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ITO8G-o0nj8 Link]'''\n\n[[Satyamev Jayate (TV series)|'''Satyamev Jayate''']]: '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9_EAPlsVYmk Link]'''\n\n'''CP Plus''': '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dyjchUCq6RE Link]'''\n\n'''[[CaratLane]]''': '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SBmOsgqmIDY Link]'''\n\n'''[[Flipkart]]''': '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yJsEzwbnZnU Link]'''\n\n'''[[Oreo|Oreo India]]''': '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y7LBHMJv2jU Link]'''\n\n'''[[Tata Sky]]''': '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0TmIxV5oi1s Link]'''\n\n'''[[Sony Max]]''': '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nQ7yRWGAmac Link]'''\n\n'''[[Line (software)|Line App]]''': '''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9tybqbv3QYI Link]'''\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year  !! Title !! Director !! Role\n|-\n|2014\n| ''[[PK (film)|PK]]'' ||[[Rajkumar Hirani]] || Jaggu's sister \n|-\n|2015\n| \"[[Big F]]\" ||[[MTV India]] || Anjali\n|-\n|2017\n| ''[[Lipstick Under My Burkha]]'' ||[[Alankrita Shrivastava]]|| Rehana Abidi\n|-\n|2018\n|''What's Your Status'' (Web Series)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=2J2yXSLgKko|title= What's Your Status{{!}}Web Series-Episode1 -Sun